{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 531 (PR #3588) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3588.","id":"vf_66e6867fd9802c31","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #531: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $F(k)$ be the minimal $N$ such that if we two-colour $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ there is a set $A$ of size $k$ such that all subset sums $\\sum_{a\\in S}a$ (for $\\emptyset\\neq S\\subseteq A$) are monochromatic. Estimate $F(k)$. Current best: Balogh, Eberhrad, Narayanan, Treglown, and Wagner \\cite{BENTW17} have improved this to\\[F(k) \\geq 2^{2^{k-1}/k}.\\]  References  [BENTW17] Balogh, J\\'{o}zsef and Eberhard, Sean and Narayanan, Bhargav and Treglown, Andrew and Wagner, Adam Zsolt, An improved lower bound for Folkman's theorem. Prize: no. Tags: number theory, ramsey theory.","id":"vf_d65c616d9b68508a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/531.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_66e6867fd9802c31","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:531","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_66e6867fd9802c31","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_d65c616d9b68508a","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_d65c616d9b68508a","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:531","trust":"signed"}],"